    <a title="Cher" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4776032-cher"><img alt="Cher" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1592359191p2/4776032.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1883398831?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cher" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cher" href="/user/show/4776032-cher">Cher</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4776032-cher?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1883398831" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9442922221012233267"><b>2.5 stars - It was alright, an average book. </b><br/><br/>An easy read about a warm and fuzzy topic, but the book became very repetitive after the first 25%. While I enjoyed the beginning, by the end I was looking forward to moving on to my next book. <br/>-------------------------------------------<br/><b>Favorite Quote:</b> While basic living standards are essential for happiness, after the baseline has been met, happiness varies more with quality of human relationships than income.<br/><br/><b>First Sentence:</b> I have the best job in th</span>
